The paper discusses an extension of Answer Set Programming (ASP) that allows for modeling problems beyond NP, which is a topic closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces quantifiers over stable models of programs, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the computational properties of the new language, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
